 'Primary mandatory Italian regulation establishing RSA (Residenza Sanitaria Assistenziale) structural standards: average 4 modules of 20-25 residents, max 6 modules/120 residents per facility, and 1 of every 3 modules (10-15 places) reserved for dementia care. A companion "Linee guida del Ministero della Sanità n. 1" (~1994, exact date uncertain across sources: 31 gennaio vs 31 marzo) elaborates organizational/management criteria but is a separate document, not ingested here pending date confirmation.',
