 '[session_2026-07-19-non-english-research-recovery-batch2] WebFetch returned 403 on all Seoul-domain and Korean news-domain pages this session. Verified via Seoul city news portal snippets, a design-industry article, and a design-database listing, cross-checked against a companion-document check that confirmed the alternative candidate (제4차 치매관리종합계획, 4th National Dementia Plan) is real but policy/service-level only with no design content -- this Seoul manual is the correct, more citable design-specific source. Medium confidence: title/publisher/program-history corroborated by multiple independent Korean sources, but no primary Seoul-government page was directly fetched.',
 'Recovered per research-handoff-non-english.md Tier-1 (wayfinding-dementia-spatial-design, KO, 7 non-EN hits) -- batch 2.',
 'Municipal design-guidance manual (not law) built around 9 design principles (safety, orientation, visibility, accessibility, sociality, continuity, memorability, activity, sensory quality). Confirmed content: color-contrast principles for aging/low-vision users (warm over cool hues; higher lightness/chroma for blue-family colors, hard for older adults to distinguish); apartment building-entrance identification via figure-ground signage contrast; outdoor-environment design guidance. Program originated 2014 (Yangcheon-gu pilot); first apartment-scale implementation 2016 (Nowon-gu, cited post-implementation study: ~30.8% reduction in cognitive-impairment incidents, ~24.4% reduction in safety accidents).',
